{"word":"ἐλεέω","slug":"ἐλεέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐλεέω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ἔλεος'><el>ἔλεος</el></a>\n<br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>like <a href='S:ἐλεαίρω'><el>ἐλεαίρω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to have pity on, shew mercy upon</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b>, attic:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> <i>to be pitied, have pity</i> or <i>mercy shewn one</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to feel pity</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}